body:
@tysonnorris @ddragosd 
Thanks for your feedback about the seed nodes, I made a small change to join the seed nodes at the startup of the `SharedDataService` service. So later you can extend the trait`SeedNodesProvider` to add kube and mesos support, or create an SPI. Are you ok with this change?

Actually this change has also helped to get rid of a _special_ seed-nodes parsing and get back the logging to the Config classes.

@vvraskin to your points: 
1 - in controller immediately, no. In controller in the near future, yes, e.g. in a mesos case we will need to use either ClusterSingleton or MemberEvent to designate a leader; we will also need to share some state within the cluster (may be able to leverage SharedDataService, or else directly use DistributedData)
2 - my concern with downing is the case where nodes are down, and not coming back (or not coming back with the same id). In this case, docs indicate that new members cannot become "up", etc, till the unreachable node is downed. So regardless of whether traffic is routed to an unreachable node, if clustering usage is affected by having an unreachable, but NOT downed node, then there will be other types of problems (e.g. can replacement nodes be added? can the cluster size be grown?). Separately from needing the ability to cause nodes to be downed, the semantics of determining down vs *temp* unreachable will be different in a cluster manager like mesos/kube, similar to the semantics of determining seed nodes.

@bwmcadams 
2. What I meant on additional complexity is that if we have cluster management outside of the actors, that could imply implementing an additional actor to monitor the health state of another nodes. I don't believe its the right timing to do that, the costs of not having the freshest state are lower then estimated effort to implement it. And I don't believe its the scope of this PR as well. 
Back to your point wrt to the measurements you mentioned. I think its a tricky one, given non-deterministic failure conditions, environment differences, etc, its difficult to guarantee that one size fits all property would work here.
